## What we're NOT building

The most important section. Explicit non-goals. Each line is a feature you've
considered and rejected, with one-line rationale.

- Feature X — reason it doesn't make this cut
- Pattern Y — why a simpler thing wins for now
- Tool Z — adopt later if a real problem demands it

If this list is empty, you haven't thought hard enough about scope.

## Open Decisions

Track unresolved questions as they surface. Each one names the phase it
blocks (or "Any phase" if cross-cutting).

- [ ] Question 1 (Phase 3 blocker)
- [ ] Question 2 (any phase)

## Sequencing Discipline

Ship each phase before starting the next. If Phase N alone turns out to be
enough, that's a valid stopping point. Don't build Phase N+2 before Phase N
is working daily.

If you start a later phase before an earlier one ships, write down WHY here:

> _(rationale — or remove this block if you're staying disciplined)_

